'''Sanatul Fuqaha''' (94 A.H.), or the '''year of the [[Fuqaha]]''', refers to the year in which many [[Islamic scholars]] and jurists died including: Saeed b. Musayyab, Urwah b. Zubair, and Saeed b. Jubayr.
